S.S.Empress of Asia, Nagasaki, Japan.
Feb.11,1933.
Dear Est Sebs.
We landed at Yokohama Wednesday
afternoon Feb.8th about three oclock. Groeger
and I went ashore as soon as we could get through with the usual procedure of rules
and regulations. We walked around town until late in the afternoon when practically
exhausted with all that exercise we came back on board to get a bath and have dinner
with the idea of starting out after dinner with a crowd of other passengers. Instead
of doing so we all sat around postponing the date of starting until it got so late
that someone suggested that which all of us had been thinking about - le going to
bed. Groeger and I had to

too much for poor Groeger. He gave me one agonizing look and then exploded blowing
his soup out as hard as the rest had been sucking theirs in. We had saki, raw fish,
rice, bamboo salad and all the other standard delicasies - all of which Groeger ate
with apparent lack of enjoymenta After lunch we drove out to the Airport which is
about the same distance from town as most Amerivan ports. It is a very good one and
will be much better when completed.
